@startuml
title 7. Workflow — tailing a transcript line through the shared engine

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "TranscriptStreamer\n::start_tailing\n(Claude | Codex)" as start
participant "TranscriptTailService\n::run (loop)" as svc
participant "<provider>\nTranscriptDecoder" as dec
participant "process_line\n(typed DTOs, Phase 1)" as pl
participant "EventSink" as sink

start -> start : open file, build decoder
start -> svc : new(decoder, label)\n.run(BufReader, stop)
note right of start
  start_tailing is now thin: open → build decoder
  → hand to the service → spawn the thread.
  Both providers share this; tail_loop is deleted.
end note

== Replay (initial catch-up) ==

loop until stop is set (Ordering::Acquire)
  svc -> svc : read_line(&mut buf)

  alt Ok(0) — EOF
    svc -> dec : on_caught_up()
    dec -> sink : flush replay snapshot\n(first EOF only)
    svc -> svc : sleep(POLL_INTERVAL)
  else Ok(n) — line has no '\n' yet
    svc -> svc : push to `partial`, continue
    note right of svc
      G3 carve-out: a tool_use line split here is
      buffered, then rejoined when the rest arrives —
      so it still emits. The old Claude loop dropped it.
    end note
  else Ok(n) — complete line
    svc -> svc : join partial, strip CRLF, skip blank
    svc -> dec : decode_line(line)
    dec -> pl : parse line ONCE → typed DTO
    note right of pl
      Codex: payload parsed ONCE, shared by the cwd
      transition AND the dispatch (the delay fix —
      was 2× per response_item line pre-C).
    end note
    pl -> sink : agent-cwd (on cwd change, deduped)
    pl -> sink : agent-tool-call / agent-turn / test-run
  else Err(e)
    svc -> svc : warn → sleep → continue
  end
end

== Live tail (after the first EOF) ==
note over svc, sink
  Same loop, now past the replay→live boundary:
  the emitter emits every snapshot live instead of
  buffering. stop() flips the AtomicBool → loop exits.
end note

@enduml
